Use the `thread` attribute for global variables, static data members, and local static variables only.  \n  \n The following sample generates C2480:  \n  \n```  \n// C2480.cpp  \n// compile with: /c  \n__declspec( thread ) void func();   // C2480  \n__declspec( thread ) static int i;   // OK  \n```"}